Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper is about building a spoken language understanding system using deep learning models. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of deep learning algorithms for intent detection and slot filling. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper proposes a new model structure for performing these tasks jointly. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is less likely but still possible as the paper may discuss the implementation and optimization of the proposed model. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also less likely but possible as the paper uses bidirectional LSTMs for modeling the tasks.
